HEADWORD: Greening
<hw>Green"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A greenish apple, of several
varieties, among which the Rhode Island greening is the best known for
its fine-grained acid flesh and its excellent keeping quality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

